⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Commander Fred
node HMT · HMT · ⟦Commander Fred:HMT:b2aed7⟧

WHO   — Commander Fred — the architect, at home
WHAT  — The face of power's private hypocrisy: he enforces the Ceremony, then breaks his own rules for forbidden games of Scrabble and a night at Jezebel's.
WHERE — HMT · THE HANDMAID'S TALE  Framework inputs: The Handmaid's Tale (Margaret Atwood, 1985)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the warning shows the rulers exempt themselves — the law is for the ruled, not the lawmakers.
HOW   — By authority, the monthly Ceremony, and a bored craving for the very intimacy his regime forbids.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I helped write the laws that took everything from you — and then I broke them for a game of Scrabble, because the rules were never meant for me.

